column5: Went to a lake close to my house for an evening walleye bite.....3 hours total time spent getting in and out...about an hour and a half fishing.    <iframe width="425" height="349" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/kj-nN3yqZXQ" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
adventure indeed! Makes me feel good to know that your not always just casting a bobber from your porch. Haha.  Sounds like a dirty but fun time... well worth it

An hour and a half to limit out on gorgeous walleye    Maaaannnnnnn you got it rough  NIcely done as usual, good sir   That launch sure looks familiar..to be more specific....wheels buried in sand sure looks familiar...
"What's that honey??  Nope, just stepping out for a bit to the Dryden area.  I'll be back in a few weeks...."
You deserve every fish you get, Simon.  Don't let Billy Bob see those submerged bearings.
great experience that I would love to do one day. awesome fish and adventure.
Simon living the dream...... I love it, becoming a highlight of my day, "I wonder what Simon is up to today"
Who needs fishing shows when you have Simon's videos.  I see Cliff is wearing one of my favorite shirts.
I guess the hard work really payed out good... great sizes of walleye Simon.... well done guys

Next time pay the $10 to launch where everyone else does...  I'm only kidding!  You guys worked hard for those fish!  Looks like getting there and back was half the adventure.  Awesome report as always!
Simon, have you been told today?  as always, nice going!

Its always been open...just no takers    LOL...tell me about it.     Ok...lemme clear something up....Lake wabigoon..."my lake"....has not been producing much in front of the house this year....i have to get in my boat and travel at least 20 minutes from the front lawn for good fishing!!!

LOL...i know of which landing you speak, actually it was not the infamous stuck truck landing......lol....that day really sucked!    Come on up Frankie.    Yeah...this Saturday is trailer and bearings inspection/repacking day    Trust me...the novelty of the adventure wears off real quick....lol.    Thanks Bubbles....i dont ever take for granted where i live.        LOL...next time i go there i want to fish for longer though.    Funny thing is ...the spot i hit the day before with multiple fish over 25" was at the local Provincial Park...guess how much it is to use the landing....lololol...$10    Told what?.....lol.
I haven't been there for years,but I reconize the landing Buddy,your secret is safe with me.
